{"type":"message","id":"36bd9eda","parentId":"97b4a532","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:53:55.483Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" Der Nutzer fragt, ob ich ein Repository auf Risiken analysieren kann, oder ob mir dafür ein Skill fehlt. Das ist eine gute Frage - ich habe tatsächlich den \"security-review\" Skill verfügbar, der genau dafür gedacht ist.\n\nIch sollte:\n1. Den security-review Skill lesen\n2. Erklären, was ich tun kann\n3. Anbieten, das Repo zu analysieren, wenn er es clont oder ich es clonen kann\n\nDer Skill \"security-review\" ist in der available_skills Liste und beschreibt sich als \"Security-focused code review patterns. Use when: (1) reviewing code for security, (2) implementing security features, (3) handling sensitive data, (4) API security.\"\n\nDas passt perfekt. Ich sollte den Skill lesen und dann anbieten, die Analyse durchzuführen.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"     Ich habe genau den richtigen Skill dafür – lass mich ihn laden:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_WwfHRy19QB6wj0k9P6rhrtjp","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/security-review/SKILL.md"}},{"type":"text","text":"  "}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"kimi-k2-thinking","usage":{"input":313,"output":244,"cacheRead":25792,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26349,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774907626554}}
{"type":"message","id":"e31ddea5","parentId":"36bd9eda","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:53:55.508Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_WwfHRy19QB6wj0k9P6rhrtjp","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: security-review\ndescription: |\n  Security-focused code review patterns. Use when: (1) reviewing code for security,\n  (2) implementing security features, (3) handling sensitive data, (4) API security.\n  \ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"security\"\n  - \"secure\"\n  - \"vulnerability\"\n  - \"audit\"\n  - \"injection\"\n  - \"auth\"\n  - \"encryption\"\n  \ncategory: security\ntags:\n  - security\n  - audit\n  - review\n  \nmetadata:\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  author: \"adapted-from-ecc\"\n  requires: []\n---\n\n# Security Review\n\n## Input Validation\n\n### SQL Injection Prevention\n```python\n# ✅ Do: Parameterized queries\ncursor.execute(\"SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = %s\", (user_id,))\n\n# ❌ Don't: String formatting\nquery = f\"SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = {user_id}\"  # VULNERABLE!\n```\n\n### Path Traversal Prevention\n```python\nimport os\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# ✅ Do: Validate and sanitize paths\nbase_path = Path(\"/safe/directory\")\nrequested_path = Path(user_input).resolve()\nif not requested_path.is_relative_to(base_path):\n    raise ValueError(\"Invalid path\")\n\n# ❌ Don't: Direct user input\nfile_path = \"/safe/directory/\" + user_input  # VULNERABLE!\n```\n\n## Authentication & Authorization\n\n### Token Handling\n```python\n# ✅ Do: Secure token storage\ntoken = os.environ.get(\"API_TOKEN\")\nif not token:\n    raise ValueError(\"API_TOKEN not set\")\n\n# ✅ Do: Token expiration check\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\n\ndef is_token_valid(token_data: dict) -> bool:\n    expires = datetime.fromisoformat(token_data[\"expires\"])\n    return datetime.now() < expires - timedelta(minutes=5)\n```\n\n### Permission Checks\n```python\n# ✅ Do: Explicit permission checks\ndef delete_resource(user: User, resource: Resource):\n    if not user.has_permission(\"resource:delete\", resource):\n        raise PermissionDenied(\"Cannot delete this resource\")\n    resource.delete()\n```\n\n## Data Protection\n\n### Encryption\n```python\nfrom cryptography.fernet import Fernet\n\n# ✅ Do: Encrypt sensitive data\nkey = Fernet.generate_key()\ncipher = Fernet(key)\nencrypted = cipher.encrypt(sensitive_data.encode())\n```\n\n### Secrets Management\n```python\n# ✅ Do: Environment variables\nimport os\n\ndatabase_url = os.environ[\"DATABASE_URL\"]\napi_key = os.environ[\"API_KEY\"]\n\n# ❌ Don't: Hardcoded secrets\nAPI_KEY = \"sk-1234567890abcdef\"  # NEVER DO THIS!\n```\n\n## Security Headers\n\n```python\n# ✅ Do: Set security headers\nresponse.headers[\"X-Content-Type-Options\"] = \"nosniff\"\nresponse.headers[\"X-Frame-Options\"] = \"DENY\"\nresponse.headers[\"Content-Security-Policy\"] = \"default-src 'self'\"\nresponse.headers[\"Strict-Transport-Security\"] = \"max-age=31536000\"\n```\n\n## Checklist\n\n### Code Review Security Checklist\n- [ ] All inputs validated and sanitized\n- [ ] SQL injection prevented (parameterized queries)\n- [ ] XSS prevented (output encoding)\n- [ ] CSRF tokens where needed\n- [ ] Authentication enforced on protected routes\n- [ ] Authorization checks for sensitive operations\n- [ ] No secrets in code or logs\n- [ ] Error messages don't leak information\n- [ ] Rate limiting on sensitive endpoints\n- [ ] Secure session handling\n\n### Common Vulnerabilities\n| CWE | Description | Prevention |\n|-----|-------------|------------|\n| CWE-79 | XSS | Output encoding |\n| CWE-89 | SQL Injection | Parameterized queries |\n| CWE-22 | Path Traversal | Input validation |\n| CWE-312 | Cleartext Storage | Encryption |\n| CWE-502 | Deserialization | Whitelist classes |\n| CWE-918 | SSRF | URL validation |\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774907635504}}
{"type":"message","id":"091a03e7","parentId":"e31ddea5","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:54:10.797Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"  Perfekt! Ich habe den security-review Skill. Ich kann also Code auf Sicherheitsrisiken analysieren. Ich sollte dem Nutzer erklären, was ich tun kann und wie wir vorgehen könnten.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"      Perfekt – ich habe den **security-review** Skill. Ich kann Code auf Risiken analysieren, aber ich brauche Zugriff auf die Dateien.\n\n## Was ich prüfen kann\n\n| Risiko-Typ | Beispiele |\n|------------|-----------|\n| **Code-Ausführung** | `os.system()`, `eval()`, `exec()`, `subprocess` mit User-Input |\n| **Datei-Operationen** | Path Traversal (`../../etc/passwd`), unvalidierte Pfade |\n| **Netzwerk** | Ungesicherte Downloads, offene Ports, SSRF |\n| **Secrets** | Hardcoded API-Keys, Passwörter, Tokens |\n| **Deserialization** | `pickle.load()`, `yaml.unsafe_load()` |\n| **Dependencies** | Bekannte CVEs in requirements |\n\n## Was ich brauche\n\nUm das Repo zu analysieren, muss ich die **Python-Dateien lesen** können. Zwei Wege:\n\n**Option A: Du clonst es selbst**\n```bash\ncd C:\\Users\\andre\\Documents\\Andrew Openclaw\ngit clone https://github.com/karpathy/autoresearch.git\n```\nDann sage mir den Pfad und ich analysiere `prepare.py`, `train.py`, etc.\n\n**Option B: Ich fetche die einzelnen Files**\nIch kann direkt von GitHub raw URLs lesen:\n- `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/karpathy/autoresearch/master/train.py`\n- `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/karpathy/autoresearch/master/prepare.py`\n\nDas ist sicher – ich lese nur, ich führe nichts aus.\n\n## Was ich dir gebe\n\n- Liste der gefundenen Risiken (nach Schweregrad)\n- Erklärung, was jeder Code macht\n- Empfehlung: Ausführen ja/nein/mit Vorsicht\n\n**Welchen Weg willst du?** Du clonst und ich analysiere lokal, oder ich hole die Files direkt von GitHub?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"kimi-k2-thinking","usage":{"input":840,"output":493,"cacheRead":26368,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27701,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774907635511}}
