{"type":"message","id":"dbc0b124","parentId":"3d6adbe6","timestamp":"2026-03-30T22:32:42.706Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_TrAPfjn8zLjOSFRbskQH0DOE","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: secure-api-client\ndescription: |\n A secure HTTP API client skill with built-in security controls.\n \n Use WHEN: Making API requests with proper authentication, rate limiting,\n timeout handling, and input validation.\n \n Trigger phrases: \"make API call\", \"fetch data from API\", \"secure HTTP request\",\n \"call REST API\", \"API client request\"\n\nmetadata:\n openclaw:\n requires:\n tools: [read, write, web_search]\n env: [API_BASE_URL, API_KEY, API_TIMEOUT]\n primaryEnv: API_KEY\n---\n\n# Secure API Client\n\n## Overview\n\nA production-ready API client implementing security best practices including:\n- Input validation with JSON Schema\n- Timeout handling on all network calls\n- Environment-based secret management\n- Rate limiting protection\n- Error handling without information leakage\n\n## Security Features\n\n### 1. Input Validation (GREEN Pattern)\n\nAll inputs validated against strict schemas:\n\n```yaml\nparameters:\n endpoint:\n   type: string\n   pattern: \"^[a-zA-Z0-9/_-]+$\"\n   maxLength: 200\n   \n method:\n   type: string\n   enum: [GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH]\n   default: GET\n   \n timeout:\n   type: integer\n   minimum: 1000\n   maximum: 60000\n   default: 30000\n```\n\n### 2. Environment-Based Secrets (GREEN Pattern)\n\n```yaml\nmetadata:\n openclaw:\n requires:\n env: [API_KEY, API_BASE_URL, API_TIMEOUT]\n```\n\nNever hardcode credentials. Always use environment variables.\n\n### 3. Timeout Protection (YELLOW Pattern - Hardened)\n\nAll network calls have mandatory timeouts:\n- Connection timeout: 5 seconds\n- Read timeout: 30 seconds (configurable)\n- Prevents DoS via hanging connections\n\n### 4. Domain Allowlist (GREEN Pattern)\n\n```yaml\nallowed_domains:\n - api.example.com\n - api.trusted-service.com\n```\n\nOnly allows requests to pre-approved domains.\n\n## Usage Examples\n\n### Basic GET Request\n\n```yaml\nMake a secure API request:\n```yaml\nsecure_request:\n method: GET\n endpoint: /users/profile\n timeout: 30000\n```\n```\n\n### POST with Data\n\n```yaml\nSend data securely:\n```yaml\nsecure_request:\n method: POST\n endpoint: /users/update\n data:\n   name: \"John Doe\"\n   email: \"john@example.com\"\n timeout: 30000\n```\n```\n\n### Handling Errors\n\nAll errors returned in structured format:\n```json\n{\n \"success\": false,\n \"error\": \"Request timeout\",\n \"code\": \"TIMEOUT_ERROR\",\n \"retryable\": true\n}\n```\n\n## Security Checklist\n\n- [x] Input validation with schemas (GREEN)\n- [x] Environment variables for secrets (GREEN)\n- [x] Timeout on all network calls (YELLOW hardened)\n- [x] Domain allowlist validation (GREEN)\n- [x] Error handling without info leakage (GREEN)\n- [x] No hardcoded credentials\n- [x] No command injection vectors\n- [x] No path traversal risks\n- [x] Rate limiting support\n\n## Pattern Classification\n\n| Pattern | Status | Implementation |\n|---------|--------|----------------|\n| Input Validation | GREEN | JSON Schema validation |\n| Environment Secrets | GREEN | Required env vars |\n| Network Timeout | YELLOW | 5s connect, 30s read |\n| Domain Allowlist | GREEN | Pre-approved domains |\n| Error Handling | GREEN | Structured errors |\n\n## References\n\nFor advanced usage, see:\n- `references/security-patterns.md` - Detailed security patterns\n- `references/api-examples.md` - Extended examples\n- `scripts/request_handler.py` - Request processing logic\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774909962702}}
{"type":"message","id":"cb57fbd1","parentId":"dbc0b124","timestamp":"2026-03-30T22:33:54.963Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"   Now I have a good example of a skill. Let me create the security-review skill based on this pattern. I'll create the directory structure and the SKILL.md file.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"  Jetzt erstelle ich den **Security Review Skill**:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_u3vgfTbg5NpCsF15cUUgDzZW","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"---\nname: security-review\ndescription: |\n  Automated security analysis skill for Python code and repositories.\n  \n  Use WHEN: Analyzing code for security vulnerabilities, reviewing repositories\n  for security risks, auditing dependencies, or assessing execution safety.\n  \n  Trigger phrases: \"security audit\", \"analyze security\", \"security review\",\n  \"check for vulnerabilities\", \"is this code safe\", \"security analysis\",\n  \"audit repository\", \"security check\"\n\ncategory: security\ntags:\n  - security\n  - audit\n  - review\n  - vulnerability\n  - code-analysis\n\nmetadata:\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  author: \"Andrew\"\n  requires: [read, write, web_fetch, web_search]\n---\n\n# Security Review Skill\n\nAutomated security analysis for Python code and repositories.\n\n## Capabilities\n\n### 1. Code Execution Risk Detection\n\nIdentifies dangerous Python functions and patterns:\n\n| Risk Category | Dangerous Patterns | Safe Alternatives |\n|--------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n| Code Injection | `eval()`, `exec()`, `compile()` | `ast.literal_eval()`, parsers |\n| Command Execution | `os.system()`, `subprocess.call()` | `subprocess.run(check=False)` with validation |\n| Dynamic Import | `__import__()`, `importlib` | Static imports, whitelist |\n| Template Injection | `str.format(**locals())` | Jinja2 with sandbox |\n\n### 2. File System Risk Detection\n\n```python\n# ❌ DANGEROUS - Path Traversal\nfile_path = \"/data/\" + user_input\n\n# ✅ SAFE - Path validation\nfrom pathlib import Path\nbase = Path(\"/data\").resolve()\nrequested = (base / user_input).resolve()\nif not requested.is_relative_to(base):\n    raise ValueError(\"Invalid path\")\n```\n\n### 3. Network Risk Detection\n\n| Check | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| URL Validation | Hardcoded vs. user-controlled URLs |\n| Protocol Check | HTTPS required, HTTP flagged |\n| Timeout Presence | All requests must have timeouts |\n| Domain Allowlist | External requests to approved domains only |\n\n### 4. Deserialization Risk Detection\n\n| Method | Risk Level | Safe Alternative |\n|--------|-----------|------------------|\n| `pickle.load()` | 🔴 HIGH | `json.load()`, `torch.load(weights_only=True)` |\n| `yaml.load()` | 🔴 HIGH | `yaml.safe_load()` |\n| `json.load()` | 🟢 LOW | Already safe |\n\n### 5. Resource Exhaustion Detection\n\nIdentifies:\n- Unbounded loops without exit conditions\n- Memory allocation without limits\n- File operations without size checks\n- Network requests without timeouts\n\n## Risk Levels\n\n| Level | Description | Action Required |\n|-------|-------------|-----------------|\n| 🟢 NONE | No security concerns | None |\n| 🟢 LOW | Minor concerns, well-controlled | Document |\n| 🟡 MEDIUM | Moderate risk, needs attention | Review |\n| 🟠 HIGH | Significant security risk | Fix before use |\n| 🔴 CRITICAL | Immediate security threat | Do not use |\n\n## Usage\n\n### Analyze a Single File\n\n```yaml\nsecurity_review:\n  target: \"path/to/file.py\"\n  checks:\n    - code_execution\n    - file_system\n    - network\n    - deserialization\n    - resources\n```\n\n### Analyze a Repository\n\n```yaml\nsecurity_review:\n  target: \"https://github.com/user/repo\"\n  depth: full\n  include_dependencies: true\n```\n\n### Checklist Mode\n\n```yaml\nsecurity_review:\n  target: \"path/to/project\"\n  mode: checklist\n  output_format: markdown\n```\n\n## Security Checklist\n\n### Python Code Checklist\n\n- [ ] No `eval()` or `exec()` usage\n- [ ] No `os.system()` or unvalidated `subprocess` calls\n- [ ] No dynamic `__import__()` with user input\n- [ ] All file paths validated (no traversal)\n- [ ] All network requests have timeouts\n- [ ] No hardcoded secrets or credentials\n- [ ] Pickle/yaml usage reviewed\n- [ ] No infinite loops without safeguards\n- [ ] Error messages don't leak sensitive info\n\n### Dependency Checklist\n\n- [ ] Dependencies pinned or minimum versions set\n- [ ] No known CVEs in dependencies\n- [ ] External indexes verified (PyPI vs. custom)\n- [ ] Compiled extensions from trusted sources\n\n## Analysis Report Format\n\n```markdown\n## Security Analysis: {target}\n\n### Executive Summary\n- Overall Risk: {LEVEL}\n- Critical Issues: {count}\n- Medium Issues: {count}\n- Low Issues: {count}\n\n### Detailed Findings\n\n#### 1. {Category} (Risk: {LEVEL})\n**Location:** {file}:{line}\n**Issue:** {description}\n**Recommendation:** {fix}\n\n### Safe Patterns Found\n- ✅ {pattern description}\n\n### Recommendations\n1. {priority recommendation}\n```\n\n## Examples\n\n### Example 1: Safe Code Pattern\n\n```python\n# ✅ GOOD - Time-bounded execution\nimport time\nMAX_RUNTIME = 300  # 5 minutes\nstart = time.time()\n\nwhile condition:\n    if time.time() - start > MAX_RUNTIME:\n        break\n    process()\n```\n\n### Example 2: Unsafe Pattern Detection\n\n```python\n# ❌ BAD - Code injection risk\ndef process_user_code(code):\n    return eval(code)  # NEVER DO THIS\n\n# ❌ BAD - Path traversal\ndef read_file(filename):\n    return open(f\"/data/{filename}\").read()\n\n# ❌ BAD - No timeout\nimport requests\nresponse = requests.get(url)  # Can hang forever\n```\n\n## References\n\n- OWASP Top 10: https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/\n- CWE/SANS Top 25: https://cwe.mitre.org/top25/\n- Python Security: https://python-security.readthedocs.io/\n","file_path":"C:/Users/andre/.openclaw/workspace/skills/security-review/SKILL.md"}},{"type":"text","text":"  "}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"kimi-k2-thinking","usage":{"input":22454,"output":1435,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23889,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774909962708}}
