{"type":"message","id":"940dd59e","parentId":"ce154d2d","timestamp":"2026-03-30T22:33:58.271Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_2vx2WsmPON3OwzcEyLl84bIg","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Skill Registry - Phase 1+ (Erweitert)\n# Auto-generiert aus skills/*/SKILL.md\n# Format: YAML 1.2\n\nversion: \"1.1\"\nlast_updated: \"2026-03-25T23:06:00+01:00\"\nauto_generated: true\ngenerator_version: \"1.1\"\n\n# Gesamtanzahl Skills\ncount: 11\n\nskills:\n  # Original 5 Skills\n  - id: \"example-weather\"\n    name: \"example-weather\"\n    description: \"Fetch weather data from external APIs\"\n    path: \"skills/example-weather\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/example-weather/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"external-api\"\n    triggers: [\"weather\", \"forecast\", \"temperature\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    \n  - id: \"secure-api-client\"\n    name: \"secure-api-client\"\n    description: \"Secure HTTP API client with built-in security controls\"\n    path: \"skills/secure-api-client\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/secure-api-client/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"security\"\n    triggers: [\"api\", \"http\", \"security\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    \n  - id: \"self-improving-andrew\"\n    name: \"self-improving-andrew\"\n    description: \"Self-improving agent that learns from corrections\"\n    path: \"skills/self-improving-andrew\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/self-improving-andrew/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"learning\"\n    triggers: [\"learning\", \"feedback\", \"correction\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    \n  - id: \"mission-control\"\n    name: \"mission-control\"\n    description: \"Command center for creating, managing, and deploying tools\"\n    path: \"skills/mission-control\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/mission-control/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: false\n    category: \"tooling\"\n    triggers: [\"tool\", \"create\", \"deploy\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    \n  - id: \"mission-control-v2\"\n    name: \"mission-control-v2\"\n    description: \"Enhanced version of mission-control\"\n    path: \"skills/mission-control-v2\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/mission-control-v2/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: false\n    category: \"tooling\"\n    triggers: [\"advanced tool\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    note: \"Contains node_modules\"\n    \n  # NEW: 6 Skills from ECC\n  - id: \"python-patterns\"\n    name: \"python-patterns\"\n    description: \"Python best practices and patterns\"\n    path: \"skills/python-patterns\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/python-patterns/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"language\"\n    triggers: [\"python\", \"pythonic\", \"py\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"adapted-from-ecc\"\n    \n  - id: \"security-review\"\n    name: \"security-review\"\n    description: \"Security-focused code review patterns\"\n    path: \"skills/security-review\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/security-review/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"security\"\n    triggers: [\"security\", \"vulnerability\", \"audit\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"adapted-from-ecc\"\n    \n  - id: \"testing-patterns\"\n    name: \"testing-patterns\"\n    description: \"Testing best practices and TDD patterns\"\n    path: \"skills/testing-patterns\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/testing-patterns/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"quality\"\n    triggers: [\"test\", \"testing\", \"tdd\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"adapted-from-ecc\"\n    \n  - id: \"api-design\"\n    name: \"api-design\"\n    description: \"REST API design patterns and OpenAPI\"\n    path: \"skills/api-design\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/api-design/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"architecture\"\n    triggers: [\"api\", \"rest\", \"endpoint\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"adapted-from-ecc\"\n    \n  - id: \"documentation\"\n    name: \"documentation\"\n    description: \"Documentation best practices\"\n    path: \"skills/documentation\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/documentation/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"communication\"\n    triggers: [\"document\", \"readme\", \"docs\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"adapted-from-ecc\"\n    \n  - id: \"refactoring\"\n    name: \"refactoring\"\n    description: \"Code refactoring patterns\"\n    path: \"skills/refactoring\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/refactoring/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"quality\"\n    triggers: [\"refactor\", \"clean up\", \"optimize\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"adapted-from-ecc\"\n    \n  - id: \"second-brain\"\n    name: \"second-brain\"\n    description: \"PARA-based knowledge management for OpenClaw sessions\"\n    path: \"second-brain\"\n    skill_file: \"second-brain/README.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: false\n    category: \"tooling\"\n    triggers: [\"second brain\", \"para\", \"knowledge\", \"obsidian\", \"sync\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"custom\"\n\n# Kategorie-Index\ncategories:\n  external-api: [\"example-weather\"]\n  security: [\"secure-api-client\", \"security-review\"]\n  learning: [\"self-improving-andrew\"]\n  tooling: [\"mission-control\", \"mission-control-v2\"]\n  language: [\"python-patterns\"]\n  quality: [\"testing-patterns\", \"refactoring\"]\n  architecture: [\"api-design\"]\n  communication: [\"documentation\"]\n\n# Agent-Zuordnungen\nagent_assignments:\n  andrew-main:\n    - example-weather\n    - secure-api-client\n    - self-improving-andrew\n    - mission-control\n    - python-patterns\n    - security-review\n    - testing-patterns\n    - api-design\n    - documentation\n    - refactoring\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774910038267}}
{"type":"message","id":"294c74a4","parentId":"940dd59e","timestamp":"2026-03-30T22:34:06.404Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"   I see there's already a security-review skill in the registry, but it's marked as \"adapted-from-ecc\". The SKILL.md file I just created will replace/update it with a more comprehensive version focused on automated analysis. Let me check if the current security-review skill exists and has content.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_QVFXpsCVt0LRbvvroPWT9XBQ","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:/Users/andre/.openclaw/workspace/skills/security-review/SKILL.md"}},{"type":"text","text":"  "}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"kimi-k2-thinking","usage":{"input":25347,"output":84,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25431,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774910038272}}
{"type":"message","id":"9831306c","parentId":"294c74a4","timestamp":"2026-03-30T22:34:06.414Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_QVFXpsCVt0LRbvvroPWT9XBQ","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: security-review\ndescription: |\n  Automated security analysis skill for Python code and repositories.\n  \n  Use WHEN: Analyzing code for security vulnerabilities, reviewing repositories\n  for security risks, auditing dependencies, or assessing execution safety.\n  \n  Trigger phrases: \"security audit\", \"analyze security\", \"security review\",\n  \"check for vulnerabilities\", \"is this code safe\", \"security analysis\",\n  \"audit repository\", \"security check\"\n\ncategory: security\ntags:\n  - security\n  - audit\n  - review\n  - vulnerability\n  - code-analysis\n\nmetadata:\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  author: \"Andrew\"\n  requires: [read, write, web_fetch, web_search]\n---\n\n# Security Review Skill\n\nAutomated security analysis for Python code and repositories.\n\n## Capabilities\n\n### 1. Code Execution Risk Detection\n\nIdentifies dangerous Python functions and patterns:\n\n| Risk Category | Dangerous Patterns | Safe Alternatives |\n|--------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n| Code Injection | `eval()`, `exec()`, `compile()` | `ast.literal_eval()`, parsers |\n| Command Execution | `os.system()`, `subprocess.call()` | `subprocess.run(check=False)` with validation |\n| Dynamic Import | `__import__()`, `importlib` | Static imports, whitelist |\n| Template Injection | `str.format(**locals())` | Jinja2 with sandbox |\n\n### 2. File System Risk Detection\n\n```python\n# ❌ DANGEROUS - Path Traversal\nfile_path = \"/data/\" + user_input\n\n# ✅ SAFE - Path validation\nfrom pathlib import Path\nbase = Path(\"/data\").resolve()\nrequested = (base / user_input).resolve()\nif not requested.is_relative_to(base):\n    raise ValueError(\"Invalid path\")\n```\n\n### 3. Network Risk Detection\n\n| Check | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| URL Validation | Hardcoded vs. user-controlled URLs |\n| Protocol Check | HTTPS required, HTTP flagged |\n| Timeout Presence | All requests must have timeouts |\n| Domain Allowlist | External requests to approved domains only |\n\n### 4. Deserialization Risk Detection\n\n| Method | Risk Level | Safe Alternative |\n|--------|-----------|------------------|\n| `pickle.load()` | 🔴 HIGH | `json.load()`, `torch.load(weights_only=True)` |\n| `yaml.load()` | 🔴 HIGH | `yaml.safe_load()` |\n| `json.load()` | 🟢 LOW | Already safe |\n\n### 5. Resource Exhaustion Detection\n\nIdentifies:\n- Unbounded loops without exit conditions\n- Memory allocation without limits\n- File operations without size checks\n- Network requests without timeouts\n\n## Risk Levels\n\n| Level | Description | Action Required |\n|-------|-------------|-----------------|\n| 🟢 NONE | No security concerns | None |\n| 🟢 LOW | Minor concerns, well-controlled | Document |\n| 🟡 MEDIUM | Moderate risk, needs attention | Review |\n| 🟠 HIGH | Significant security risk | Fix before use |\n| 🔴 CRITICAL | Immediate security threat | Do not use |\n\n## Usage\n\n### Analyze a Single File\n\n```yaml\nsecurity_review:\n  target: \"path/to/file.py\"\n  checks:\n    - code_execution\n    - file_system\n    - network\n    - deserialization\n    - resources\n```\n\n### Analyze a Repository\n\n```yaml\nsecurity_review:\n  target: \"https://github.com/user/repo\"\n  depth: full\n  include_dependencies: true\n```\n\n### Checklist Mode\n\n```yaml\nsecurity_review:\n  target: \"path/to/project\"\n  mode: checklist\n  output_format: markdown\n```\n\n## Security Checklist\n\n### Python Code Checklist\n\n- [ ] No `eval()` or `exec()` usage\n- [ ] No `os.system()` or unvalidated `subprocess` calls\n- [ ] No dynamic `__import__()` with user input\n- [ ] All file paths validated (no traversal)\n- [ ] All network requests have timeouts\n- [ ] No hardcoded secrets or credentials\n- [ ] Pickle/yaml usage reviewed\n- [ ] No infinite loops without safeguards\n- [ ] Error messages don't leak sensitive info\n\n### Dependency Checklist\n\n- [ ] Dependencies pinned or minimum versions set\n- [ ] No known CVEs in dependencies\n- [ ] External indexes verified (PyPI vs. custom)\n- [ ] Compiled extensions from trusted sources\n\n## Analysis Report Format\n\n```markdown\n## Security Analysis: {target}\n\n### Executive Summary\n- Overall Risk: {LEVEL}\n- Critical Issues: {count}\n- Medium Issues: {count}\n- Low Issues: {count}\n\n### Detailed Findings\n\n#### 1. {Category} (Risk: {LEVEL})\n**Location:** {file}:{line}\n**Issue:** {description}\n**Recommendation:** {fix}\n\n### Safe Patterns Found\n- ✅ {pattern description}\n\n### Recommendations\n1. {priority recommendation}\n```\n\n## Examples\n\n### Example 1: Safe Code Pattern\n\n```python\n# ✅ GOOD - Time-bounded execution\nimport time\nMAX_RUNTIME = 300  # 5 minutes\nstart = time.time()\n\nwhile condition:\n    if time.time() - start > MAX_RUNTIME:\n        break\n    process()\n```\n\n### Example 2: Unsafe Pattern Detection\n\n```python\n# ❌ BAD - Code injection risk\ndef process_user_code(code):\n    return eval(code)  # NEVER DO THIS\n\n# ❌ BAD - Path traversal\ndef read_file(filename):\n    return open(f\"/data/{filename}\").read()\n\n# ❌ BAD - No timeout\nimport requests\nresponse = requests.get(url)  # Can hang forever\n```\n\n## References\n\n- OWASP Top 10: https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/\n- CWE/SANS Top 25: https://cwe.mitre.org/top25/\n- Python Security: https://python-security.readthedocs.io/\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774910046411}}
