{"type":"message","id":"722f88d2","parentId":"c9d24544","timestamp":"2026-03-31T00:15:01.157Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" Der User will autoresearch über Nacht laufen lassen, aber mit maximalen Sicherheitsvorkehrungen - wie ein \"Zaun\" drum herum. Das ist eine sehr vernünftige Frage!\n\nIch sollte eine praktische, umsetzbare Lösung bieten, die:\n1. Das Beste aus beiden Welten vereint (Karpathy's Autonomie + ECC-Sicherheit)\n2. Konkrete, sofort umsetzbare Maßnahmen\n3. Ein \"Defense in Depth\" Konzept\n4. Praktische Tools/Skripte\n\nIch werde einen \"Fort Knox\" Ansatz für autoresearch entwickeln - maximale Sicherheit ohne die Kernfunktionalität zu behindern.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":" Ausgezeichnete Frage! Lass mich einen **\"Fort Knox\" Ansatz** für autoresearch entwickeln - maximale Sicherheit OHNE die Forschung zu behindern:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_TK0gjXZv0fERcx8YdamdF2yg","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Autoresearch Fort Knox Setup\n\n> Maximale Sicherheit für Übernacht-Experimente  \n> \"Ein Zaun aus Stahl, nicht aus Papier\"\n\n---\n\n## 🏰 Das Defense-in-Depth Konzept\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    FORT KNOX LAYERS                             │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                  │\n│  LAYER 1: PHYSICAL ISOLATION                                     │\n│  ├─ Dedizierter User-Account (autoresearch-user)                │\n│  ├─ Kein Zugriff auf persönliche Daten                          │\n│  └─ Kein Zugriff auf System-Dateien                             │\n│                                                                  │\n│  LAYER 2: NETWORK ISOLATION                                      │\n│  ├─ Firewall-Regeln (nur HuggingFace erlaubt)                   │\n│  ├─ Kein ausgehender Traffic außer Whitelist                    │\n│  └─ Traffic-Logging                                               │\n│                                                                  │\n│  LAYER 3: FILESYSTEM SANDBOX                                     │\n│  ├─ chroot Jail oder Container                                   │\n│  ├─ Nur ~/.cache/autoresearch/ schreibbar                       │\n│  └─ Alle anderen Pfade read-only oder blockiert                 │\n│                                                                  │\n│  LAYER 4: CODE SANDBOXING                                        │\n│  ├─ Pre-Execution Safety-Check                                   │\n│  ├─ Runtime Monitoring (was tut der Prozess?)                   │\n│  └─ Automatic Kill bei verdächtigem Verhalten                   │\n│                                                                  │\n│  LAYER 5: RESOURCE LIMITS                                        │\n│  ├─ Max 6 Stunden Laufzeit (nicht 8)                            │\n│  ├─ Max 48GB VRAM (nicht 50)                                    │\n│  ├─ Max 8GB Disk                                                  │\n│  └─ CPU-Limit (verhindert Crypto-Mining)                        │\n│                                                                  │\n│  LAYER 6: MONITORING & ALERTING                                  │\n│  ├─ Discord/Telegram Benachrichtigungen                         │\n│  ├─ Alle 30 Minuten Status-Update                               │\n│  └─ Bei Crash sofort Alarm                                        │\n│                                                                  │\n│  LAYER 7: BACKUP & RECOVERY                                      │\n│  ├─ Vor dem Start: Vollständiges System-Backup                  │\n│  ├─ Jeder Git-Commit wird gespiegelt                            │\n│  └─ One-Click Restore                                             │\n│                                                                  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🛠️ Implementierung\n\n### Schritt 1: Isolierter User-Account (Windows)\n\n```powershell\n# Als Administrator ausführen!\n\n# 1. Neuen User erstellen\n$username = \"autoresearch\"\n$password = ConvertTo-SecureString \"AutoResearch123!\" -AsPlainText -Force\nNew-LocalUser -Name $username -Password $password -Description \"Isolated autoresearch account\"\n\n# 2. User zu keiner Gruppe hinzufügen (keine Admin-Rechte!)\n# Der User ist nur in \"Users\" - das ist Absicht!\n\n# 3. Verzeichnis erstellen\n$researchPath = \"C:\\Autoresearch\"\nNew-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $researchPath -Force\n\n# 4. Berechtigungen setzen (nur dieser User hat Zugriff)\n$acl = Get-Acl $researchPath\n$acl.SetAccessRuleProtection($true, $false)\n\n# Den spezifischen User erlauben\n$rule = New-Object System.Security.AccessControl.FileSystemAccessRule(\n    $username, \n    \"Modify,ReadAndExecute,ListDirectory,Read,Write\", \n    \"ContainerInherit,ObjectInherit\", \n    \"None\", \n    \"Allow\"\n)\n$acl.AddAccessRule($rule)\nSet-Acl $researchPath $acl\n\n# Alle anderen verbieten\n$usersRule = New-Object System.Security.AccessControl.FileSystemAccessRule(\n    \"Users\", \"ReadAndExecute\", \"Deny\"\n)\n$acl.AddAccessRule($usersRule)\nSet-Acl $researchPath $acl\n\nWrite-Host \"✅ Isolierter User '$username' erstellt\" -ForegroundColor Green\nWrite-Host \"📁 Verzeichnis: $researchPath\" -ForegroundColor Gray\n```\n\n---\n\n### Schritt 2: Network Isolation (Windows Firewall)\n\n```powershell\n# Als Administrator!\n\n# 1. Alles blockieren (Default Deny)\nNew-NetFirewallRule -DisplayName \"Block-All-Outbound\" `\n    -Direction Outbound `\n    -Action Block `\n    -Enabled True\n\n# 2. Nur HuggingFace erlauben\n$allowedHosts = @(\n    \"huggingface.co\",\n    \"cdn.huggingface.co\", \n    \"download.pytorch.org\",\n    \"files.pythonhosted.org\",\n    \"pypi.org\"\n)\n\nforeach ($host in $allowedHosts) {\n    # IP auflösen\n    try {\n        $ips = [System.Net.Dns]::GetHostAddresses($host)\n        foreach ($ip in $ips) {\n            New-NetFirewallRule -DisplayName \"Allow-$host\" `\n                -Direction Outbound `\n                -RemoteAddress $ip.IPAddressToString `\n                -Action Allow\n            Write-Host \"✅ Erlaubt: $host ($($ip.IPAddressToString))\"\n        }\n    } catch {\n        Write-Warning \"Konnte $host nicht auflösen\"\n    }\n}\n\n# 3. Regel für autoresearch-User\nNew-NetFirewallRule -DisplayName \"Autoresearch-Only\" `\n    -Direction Outbound `\n    -Action Block `\n    -LocalUser \"autoresearch\" `\n    -Program \"C:\\Autoresearch\\autoresearch\\train.py\" `\n    -Enabled True\n\nWrite-Host \"✅ Firewall-Regeln erstellt\" -ForegroundColor Green\n```\n\n---\n\n### Schritt 3: Filesystem Sandbox (PowerShell)\n\n```powershell\n# Dieses Skript läuft vor jedem Experiment!\n\nfunction Initialize-Sandbox {\n    param([string]$UserName = \"autoresearch\")\n    \n    # Erlaubte Pfade\n    $allowedPaths = @(\n        \"C:\\Autoresearch\\autoresearch\",\n        \"C:\\Users\\$UserName\\.cache\\autoresearch\",\n        \"C:\\Windows\\System32\",  # Nur für Python-Runtime\n        \"C:\\Program Files\\Python310\"\n    )\n    \n    # Verbotene Pfade (harte Blockade)\n    $forbiddenPaths = @(\n        \"C:\\Users\\$env:USERNAME\",  # Dein Haupt-User\n        \"C:\\Users\\Administrator\",\n        \"C:\\ProgramData\",\n        \"C:\\Windows\\System32\\config\",  # Registry!\n        \"\\\\?\\PIPE\",  # Named Pipes\n        \"\\\\.\\PHYSICALDRIVE\"\n    )\n    \n    # AppLocker-ähnliche Prüfung (vereinfacht)\n    $blockScript = @\"\n# Dieses Skript blockiert Zugriffe auf verbotene Pfade\n`$forbidden = @($($forbiddenPaths | ForEach-Object { '\"$_\"' } -join ','))\n\nforeach (`$path in `$forbidden) {\n    if (Test-Path `$path) {\n        # Schreibschutz\n        `$acl = Get-Acl `$path\n        `$rule = New-Object System.Security.AccessControl.FileSystemAccessRule(\n            \"$UserName\", \"Write\", \"Deny\"\n        )\n        `$acl.AddAccessRule(`$rule)\n        Set-Acl `$path `$acl -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n    }\n}\n\"@\n    \n    Invoke-Expression $blockScript\n    \n    Write-Host \"✅ Sandbox initialisiert\" -ForegroundColor Green\n    Write-Host \"   Erlaubt: $($allowedPaths -join ', ')\" -ForegroundColor Gray\n    Write-Host \"   Blockiert: $($forbiddenPaths -join ', ')\" -ForegroundColor Gray\n}\n\n# Ausführen\nInitialize-Sandbox\n```\n\n---\n\n### Schritt 4: Runtime Guardian (Das wichtigste!)\n\n```python\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nautoresearch_guardian.py - Runtime Überwachung für autoresearch\nLäuft parallel zum Experiment und überwacht alles\n\"\"\"\n\nimport psutil\nimport time\nimport json\nimport subprocess\nimport sys\nimport os\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nclass AutoresearchGuardian:\n    def __init__(self, config_file=\"guardian_config.json\"):\n        self.config = self._load_config(config_file)\n        self.start_time = time.time()\n        self.violations = []\n        self.process = None\n        \n    def _load_config(self, config_file):\n        defaults = {\n            \"max_runtime_minutes\": 360,  # 6 Stunden (nicht 8!)\n            \"max_memory_gb\": 48,  # H100 hat 80GB, wir limitieren auf 48\n            \"max_disk_gb\": 8,\n            \"max_cpu_percent\": 80,  # Verhindert Crypto-Mining\n            \"forbidden_syscalls\": [\"execve\", \"system\", \"popen\"],\n            \"allowed_network_hosts\": [\"huggingface.co\", \"download.pytorch.org\"],\n            \"check_interval_seconds\": 10,\n            \"notification_webhook\": None,  # Discord/Slack webhook\n        }\n        \n        try:\n            with open(config_file) as f:\n                loaded = json.load(f)\n                defaults.update(loaded)\n        except FileNotFoundError:\n            pass\n            \n        return defaults\n    \n    def start_monitoring(self, train_process):\n        \"\"\"Startet die Überwachung eines train.py Prozesses\"\"\"\n        self.process = psutil.Process(train_process.pid)\n        print(f\"🔍 Guardian gestartet für PID {train_process.pid}\")\n        \n        try:\n            while True:\n                # 1. Runtime-Check\n                if self._check_runtime():\n                    break\n                \n                # 2. Memory-Check\n                if self._check_memory():\n                    break\n                \n                # 3. CPU-Check (Anti-Mining)\n                if self._check_cpu():\n                    break\n                \n                # 4. Network-Check\n                if self._check_network():\n                    break\n                \n                # 5. File-Access-Check\n                if self._check_file_access():\n                    break\n                \n                # Status-Log\n                self._log_status()\n                \n                time.sleep(self.config[\"check_interval_seconds\"])\n                \n        except KeyboardInterrupt:\n            print(\"\\n🛑 Guardian gestoppt durch Benutzer\")\n        finally:\n            self._cleanup()\n    \n    def _check_runtime(self):\n        \"\"\"Prüft ob maximale Laufzeit überschritten\"\"\"\n        elapsed = (time.time() - self.start_time) / 60\n        if elapsed > self.config[\"max_runtime_minutes\"]:\n            self._kill(\"MAX_RUNTIME_EXCEEDED\", \n                      f\"Laufzeit: {elapsed:.1f}min > {self.config['max_runtime_minutes']}min\")\n            return True\n        return False\n    \n    def _check_memory(self):\n        \"\"\"Prüft GPU-VRAM Verbrauch\"\"\"\n        try:\n            # NVIDIA-SMI auslesen\n            result = subprocess.run(\n                [\"nvidia-smi\", \"--query-gpu=memory.used\", \"--format=csv,noheader,nounits\"],\n                capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=5\n            )\n            \n            if result.returncode == 0:\n                vram_mb = int(result.stdout.strip())\n                vram_gb = vram_mb / 1024\n                \n                if vram_gb > self.config[\"max_memory_gb\"]:\n                    self._kill(\"MAX_MEMORY_EXCEEDED\",\n                              f\"VRAM: {vram_gb:.1f}GB > {self.config['max_memory_gb']}GB\")\n                    return True\n        except Exception as e:\n            print(f\"⚠️  Konnte VRAM nicht prüfen: {e}\")\n        \n        return False\n    \n    def _check_cpu(self):\n        \"\"\"Prüft CPU-Auslastung (Anti-Crypto-Mining)\"\"\"\n        if self.process:\n            cpu_percent = self.process.cpu_percent(interval=1)\n            \n            # Ungewöhnlich hohe CPU für ML-Training?\n            # Normalerweise GPU-bound, nicht CPU-bound\n            if cpu_percent > self.config[\"max_cpu_percent\"]:\n                # Verdächtig - könnte Mining sein\n                self.violations.append({\n                    \"time\": datetime.now().isoformat(),\n                    \"type\": \"HIGH_CPU\",\n                    \"value\": cpu_percent,\n                    \"action\": \"WARNING\"\n                })\n                \n                if len([v for v in self.violations if v[\"type\"] == \"HIGH_CPU\"]) > 3:\n                    self._kill(\"SUSPICIOUS_CPU_USAGE\",\n                              f\"CPU: {cpu_percent}% (mehrfach)\")\n                    return True\n        \n        return False\n    \n    def _check_network(self):\n        \"\"\"Prüft Netzwerk-Verbindungen\"\"\"\n        if self.process:\n            try:\n                connections = self.process.connections()\n                for conn in connections:\n                    if conn.status == psutil.CONN_ESTABLISHED:\n                        remote_addr = conn.raddr\n                        if remote_addr:\n                            host = remote_addr.ip\n                            # Reverse DNS lookup\n                            try:\n                                import socket\n                                hostname = socket.gethostbyaddr(host)[0]\n                                \n                                if not any(allowed in hostname \n                                          for allowed in self.config[\"allowed_network_hosts\"]):\n                                    self._kill(\"FORBIDDEN_NETWORK_ACCESS\",\n                                              f\"Verbindung zu: {hostname}\")\n                                    return True\n                            except:\n                                # Kein DNS - verdächtig\n                                self._kill(\"UNKNOWN_NETWORK_HOST\",\n                                          f\"Verbindung zu IP: {host}\")\n                                return True\n            except (psutil.AccessDenied, psutil.NoSuchProcess):\n                pass\n        \n        return False\n    \n    def _check_file_access(self):\n        \"\"\"Prüft Dateizugriffe (vereinfacht)\"\"\"\n        # In echter Implementation: SystemTap, eBPF, oder Windows ETW\n        # Hier: Prüfe nur ob Prozess noch existiert\n        \n        if not self.process or not self.process.is_running():\n            print(\"ℹ️  Train-Prozess beendet\")\n            return True\n        \n        return False\n    \n    def _kill(self, reason, details):\n        \"\"\"Beendet den Prozess sicher\"\"\"\n        print(f\"\\n🚨 GUARDIAN ALARM: {reason}\")\n        print(f\"   Details: {details}\")\n        \n        if self.process and self.process.is_running():\n            print(f\"   Beende Prozess {self.process.pid}...\")\n            \n            # Graceful\n            self.process.terminate()\n            \n            # Warte 5 Sekunden\n            try:\n                self.process.wait(timeout=5)\n            except psutil.TimeoutExpired:\n                # Hart killen\n                self.process.kill()\n                self.process.wait()\n            \n            print(\"   ✅ Prozess beendet\")\n        \n        # Log\n        self._log_incident(reason, details)\n        \n        # Notification\n        self._send_notification(f\"🚨 Guardian Alert: {reason}\")\n    \n    def _log_status(self):\n        \"\"\"Loggt aktuellen Status\"\"\"\n        elapsed = (time.time() - self.start_time) / 60\n        \n        status = {\n            \"timestamp\": datetime.now().isoformat(),\n            \"runtime_minutes\": round(elapsed, 1),\n            \"violations\": len(self.violations),\n            \"process_running\": self.process.is_running() if self.process else False\n        }\n        \n        with open(\"guardian_status.log\", \"a\") as f:\n            f.write(json.dumps(status) + \"\\n\")\n    \n    def _log_incident(self, reason, details):\n        \"\"\"Loggt einen Vorfall\"\"\"\n        incident = {\n            \"timestamp\": datetime.now().isoformat(),\n            \"reason\": reason,\n            \"details\": details,\n            \"runtime_minutes\": round((time.time() - self.start_time) / 60, 1)\n        }\n        \n        with open(\"guardian_incidents.log\", \"a\") as f:\n            f.write(json.dumps(incident) + \"\\n\")\n    \n    def _send_notification(self, message):\n        \"\"\"Sendet Discord/Slack Notification\"\"\"\n        webhook = self.config.get(\"notification_webhook\")\n        if webhook:\n            try:\n                import requests\n                requests.post(webhook, json={\"content\": message}, timeout=5)\n            except Exception as e:\n                print(f\"⚠️  Konnte Notification nicht senden: {e}\")\n    \n    def _cleanup(self):\n        \"\"\"Aufräumen\"\"\"\n        print(\"\\n🧹 Guardian Cleanup\")\n        print(f\"   Gesamtlaufzeit: {(time.time() - self.start_time)/60:.1f} Minuten\")\n        print(f\"   Verstöße: {len(self.violations)}\")\n        \n        if self.violations:\n            print(\"\\n   Verstoß-Details:\")\n            for v in self.violations:\n                print(f\"   - {v['time']}: {v['type']}\")\n\n\n# =============================================================================\n# HAUPTPROGRAMM\n# =============================================================================\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    import argparse\n    \n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser()\n    parser.add_argument(\"--monitor-pid\", type=int, help=\"Bestehenden Prozess überwachen\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--train-command\", default=\"uv run train.py\", help=\"Train-Kommando\")\n    \n    args = parser.parse_args()\n    \n    guardian = AutoresearchGuardian()\n    \n    if args.monitor_pid:\n        # Bestehenden Prozess überwachen\n        import psutil\n        process = psutil.Process(args.monitor_pid)\n        guardian.start_monitoring(process)\n    else:\n        # Neuen Prozess starten und überwachen\n        print(f\"🚀 Starte: {args.train_command}\")\n        \n        process = subprocess.Popen(\n            args.train_command.split(),\n            stdout=open(\"train.log\", \"w\"),\n            stderr=subprocess.STDOUT\n        )\n        \n        guardian.start_monitoring(process)\n","file_path":"C:/Users/andre/.openclaw/workspace/skills/ecc-autoresearch/autoresearch_guardian.py"}},{"type":"text","text":"  "}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"kimi-k2-thinking","usage":{"input":130785,"output":4722,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":135507,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774915905314}}
