{"type":"message","id":"c8294553","parentId":"af7368b4","timestamp":"2026-03-31T02:20:10.430Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" Der User hat einen \"Pre-compaction memory flush\" Trigger bekommen. Das bedeutet, ich soll wichtige Informationen aus dieser Session in die Datei `memory/2026-03-31.md` speichern.\n\nWas ist heute passiert?\n1. Sicherheitsanalyse von karpathy/autoresearch\n2. Erstellung eines Security-Review Skills\n3. Analyse des ECC Second Brain Frameworks (PowerShell)\n4. Vergleich: Karpathy vs ECC Autoresearch\n5. Fort Knox Setup Versuche (viele Fehler, viele Learnings)\n6. Telegram Bot Setup\n7. PowerShell Learnings (12 Punkte dokumentiert)\n\nDie wichtigsten durable memories:\n- Die PowerShell Learnings (sind bereits in `memory/2026-03-31-learning-report-powershell.md` gespeichert)\n- Der Fort Knox Ansatz mit den 7 Schutzschichten\n- Die erfolgreichen Berechtigungs-Patterns (takeown/icacls)\n- Die Telegram-Integration\n\nIch sollte eine Zusammenfassung in `memory/2026-03-31.md` speichern. Die Datei existiert bereits (wurde heute schon erstellt für die Karpathy-Analyse), also muss ich APPENDen.\n\nIch werde eine kurze Zusammenfassung der heutigen Arbeit speichern.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_4r5yQOkxAVz5rrPKflLQNzrb","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"\n## Session Summary - 2026-03-31 (Early Morning)\n\n**Time:** 00:00 - 04:18  \n**Focus:** Autoresearch Fort Knox Implementation & PowerShell Security Setup\n\n### Key Achievements:\n1. **Security Analysis Complete:** Analyzed karpathy/autoresearch repository (Risk: LOW)\n2. **Security-Review Skill v2.0:** Created with multi-language support and timeout prevention\n3. **ECC Framework Analysis:** Reviewed PowerShell security (Risk: LOW)\n4. **Fort Knox Architecture:** Designed 7-layer defense system for autonomous AI research\n5. **Telegram Integration:** Bot created (@andre_autoresearch_bot) with notifications\n6. **PowerShell Learnings:** Documented 12 systematic errors and solutions\n\n### Critical Learnings Documented:\n- Reserved words ($host, $input) must never be used as variables\n- ASCII-only output (no emojis) for Windows compatibility\n- ACL handling: Always use takeown + icacls, never .NET ACL objects directly\n- Correct permission sequence: takeown → icacls → copy → finalize\n- Here-strings problematic for JSON - use one-liners instead\n- Locale issues: \"Administrators\" vs \"Administratoren\" - use SIDs or $env:USERNAME\n\n### Working Pattern Found:\n```powershell\ntakeown /F \"C:\folder\" /R /D Y\nicacls \"C:\folder\" /grant \"username:(OI)(CI)F\"\n```\n\n### Status:\n- Telegram Bot: ✅ Configured (Token + Chat ID set)\n- Guardian Script: ✅ Ready with Telegram support\n- Fort Knox Setup: ⚠️ In progress (permission issues resolved, implementation pending)\n- Next Step: Complete manual setup using documented patterns tomorrow\n\n### Files Created:\n- `skills/security-review/SKILL.md` (v2.0)\n- `skills/ecc-autoresearch/` (Guardian, Safety-Checker, Sync scripts)\n- `memory/2026-03-31-learning-report-powershell.md` (12 error patterns)\n- `memory/2026-03-31-karpathy-autoresearch-full-analysis.md`\n\n**Note:** User exhausted after 4+ hours debugging PowerShell permission issues. All solutions documented for fresh start tomorrow.\n","file_path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-31.md"}},{"type":"text","text":"  "}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"kimi-k2-thinking","usage":{"input":173538,"output":838,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":174376,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774923511110}}
