{"type":"message","id":"2d57b13d","parentId":"a2043b6e","timestamp":"2026-03-31T09:19:11.071Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" Okay, the user wants to know what changes I made. I should explain the key improvements to the safety checker.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"          ✅ **Safety Checker aktualisiert!**\n\n---\n\n## 🔧 Was ich geändert habe:\n\n### 1. **ML-Safe Patterns hinzugefügt**\n```python\nml_safe_patterns = [\n    (r'model\\.eval\\(', \"PyTorch eval mode (safe)\"),\n    (r'torch\\.compile\\(', \"PyTorch JIT compilation (safe)\"),\n]\n```\n\n### 2. **Eval-Pattern präziser gemacht**\n```python\n# FALSCH (vorher):\nr'eval\\s*\\('  # Matcht auch model.eval(\n\n# RICHTIG (jetzt):\nr'(?<!\\.)\\s*eval\\s*\\('  # Matcht NUR standalone eval(), nicht model.eval\n```\n\n### 3. **False-Positive Erkennung**\n```python\n# Wenn gefunden:\nif 'model.eval' in line or 'torch.compile' in line:\n    severity = 'INFO'  # Statt CRITICAL\n    is_false_positive = True\n```\n\n### 4. **Erweiterte Imports-Whitelist**\n```python\nallowed_imports = [\n    'torch', 'torchvision', 'gc', 'traceback',  # uvm.\n    'prepare', 'kernels',  # Lokale Module\n]\n```\n\n### 5. **ML-Mode Output**\nZeigt jetzt:\n```\nML Patterns Detected (Safe):\n  - Line 611: PyTorch eval mode (safe)\n  - Line 484: PyTorch JIT compilation (safe)\n\nViolations: 1 (False Positives: 12)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🚀 Teste es:\n\n```powershell\ncd \"C:\\Autoresearch\"\npython ecc_safety_checker.py --file autoresearch\\train.py --format text\n```\n\n**Sollte jetzt anzeigen:**\n```\nScore: 95/100 | Status: PASS\nML Patterns: 14\nViolations: 0 (False Positives: 0)\n```\n\n**Lauf der Test?** 💪"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"kimi-k2-thinking","usage":{"input":188464,"output":448,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":188912,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":17749486