{"type":"message","id":"5a53946d","parentId":"5f5933bc","timestamp":"2026-03-31T23:29:45.164Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" Der User will das Projekt pausieren und den Fortschritt speichern. Er gibt zusätzliche Info: GTX 980M (alte GPU, nicht H100).\n\nIch soll:\n1. Den aktuellen Stand dokumentieren\n2. Das Projekt ordentlich pausieren/parken\n3. Wichtige Infos für die Wiederaufnahme sammeln\n\nWas haben wir bisher:\n- Fort Knox Setup läuft (isoliert)\n- Guardian V2 bereit\n- Telegram konfiguriert\n- Autoresearch geklont\n- Dependencies installiert\n- GTX 980M (wichtig: keine H100, weniger VRAM!)\n\nIch muss in MEMORY.md speichern und eine Zusammenfassung geben.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"        Verstanden! Lass mich alles **ordentlich dokumentieren** für die Wiederaufnahme:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_lH71TsBsChTVfDkYtB1Uch0Q","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"\n\n---\n\n## Project Status: karpathy/autoresearch on Windows with GTX 980M\n\n**Last Updated:** 2026-04-01 01:27  \n**Status:** PAUSED - Ready for overnight runs  \n**Hardware:** GTX 980M (4GB VRAM) - IMPORTANT: Not H100!\n\n### ✅ Completed Setup\n\n#### 1. Fort Knox Security Infrastructure\n- **Isolated User:** `autoresearch` created with restricted permissions\n- **Directory:** `C:\\Autoresearch\\` with proper ACLs\n- **Firewall:** Configured (HuggingFace, PyTorch, PyPI whitelisted)\n- **Guardian V2:** Active with network monitoring (paranoid mode)\n- **Telegram Bot:** Configured and tested (@andre_autoresearch_bot)\n\n#### 2. Software Stack\n- **Git:** Installed and functional\n- **Python:** 3.10+ via uv\n- **Dependencies:** `uv sync` completed in `C:\\Autoresearch\\autoresearch\\`\n- **Data:** `prepare.py` executed (tokenizer trained, data cached)\n\n#### 3. Safety Systems\n- **Safety Checker:** Enhanced with ML-safe patterns (false positive handling)\n- **Guardian V2:** Network monitoring, Telegram alerts, auto-kill on violations\n- **Resource Limits:** 6h runtime, 48GB RAM (adjusted for GTX 980M)\n\n### ⚠️ CRITICAL: Hardware Limitations (GTX 980M)\n\n**Difference from Reference Setup (H100):**\n| Spec | H100 (Reference) | GTX 980M (Your Setup) |\n|------|------------------|----------------------|\n| VRAM | 80 GB | 4 GB |\n| Compute | ~1000 TFLOPS | ~5 TFLOPS |\n| Time Budget | 5 min default | 5 min (same) |\n| Batch Size | Large (524K tokens) | MUST REDUCE |\n\n**Required Adjustments for GTX 980M:**\n```python\n# In train.py BEFORE first run:\nDEVICE_BATCH_SIZE = 8        # Default: 128 - REDUCE TO 8 or 16\nTOTAL_BATCH_SIZE = 2**14     # Default: 2**19 (~524K) - REDUCE to 16K\nDEPTH = 4                    # Default: 8 - REDUCE for less VRAM\nMAX_SEQ_LEN = 512            # In prepare.py - REDUCE from 2048\n```\n\n**Why:** GTX 980M has only 4GB VRAM vs 80GB on H100. Default config will OOM (Out of Memory).\n\n### 📋 Next Steps When Resuming\n\n#### Immediate (Before First Real Run):\n1. **Adjust hyperparameters** in `train.py` for 4GB VRAM:\n   ```powershell\n   cd C:\\Autoresearch\\autoresearch\n   notepad train.py\n   # Change: DEVICE_BATCH_SIZE = 16 (line ~260)\n   # Change: TOTAL_BATCH_SIZE = 2**15 (line ~19)\n   # Change: DEPTH = 6 (line ~42)\n   ```\n\n2. **Adjust in prepare.py:**\n   ```powershell\n   notepad prepare.py\n   # Change: MAX_SEQ_LEN = 512 (line ~23)\n   # Change: EVAL_TOKENS = 10 * 524288 (line ~24)\n   ```\n\n3. **Test with minimal config:**\n   ```powershell\n   cd C:\\Autoresearch\n   python autoresearch_guardian_v2.py --train-command \"uv run train.py\"\n   # Should complete 5 min without OOM\n   ```\n\n#### Overnight Run (When Ready):\n```powershell\ncd C:\\Autoresearch\npython autoresearch_guardian_v2.py --train-command \"uv run train.py\"\n# Will run for 5 min, auto-stop, Telegram notifications\n```\n\n### 🔧 Known Issues & Solutions\n\n| Issue | Solution |\n|-------|----------|\n| Safety Checker false positives | Use Guardian V2 instead (runtime monitoring) |\n| GTX 980M VRAM limitations | Reduce batch size, depth, seq_len (see above) |\n| German Windows locale | Use `$env:USERNAME` instead of \"Administrators\" |\n| PowerShell execution policy | Run as Administrator |\n\n### 📁 Important Paths\n\n```\nC:\\Autoresearch\\                    # Base directory\n├── autoresearch\\                   # Git repo (karpathy/autoresearch)\n│   ├── train.py                    # EDIT THIS for GTX 980M\n│   ├── prepare.py                  # EDIT THIS for GTX 980M\n│   └── ...\n├── autoresearch_guardian_v2.py     # Runtime guardian\n├── guardian_simple.py              # Fallback guardian\n├── ecc_safety_checker.py           # Code validator\n└── logs\\                           # Guardian logs\n```\n\n### 🎯 Success Criteria\n\n**First Test (5 min):**\n- [ ] No OOM errors\n- [ ] Telegram notifications received\n- [ ] val_bpb calculated (any value is OK for first run)\n- [ ] Process terminates cleanly after 5 min\n\n**Overnight Run (6h):**\n- [ ] 50+ experiments completed\n- [ ] No Guardian violations\n- [ ] Best val_bpb < 1.0 (improvement over baseline)\n- [ ] No system crashes\n\n### 🚨 Critical Reminders\n\n1. **GTX 980M is SLOW** - Expect ~2-4 experiments/hour vs 12/hour on H100\n2. **Temperature** - Monitor GPU temp (GTX 980M runs hot under sustained load)\n3. **Power** - Ensure laptop is plugged in, power settings on \"High Performance\"\n4. **Network** - WiFi must be stable (Guardian will alert if disconnected)\n\n### 📚 Reference Materials\n\n- **Original Repo:** https://github.com/karpathy/autoresearch\n- **Learning Report:** `memory/2026-03-31-learning-report-powershell.md`\n- **Fort Knox Scripts:** `skills/ecc-autoresearch/`\n- **Telegram Bot:** @andre_autoresearch_bot\n\n### 💾 Backup Status\n\n- **Git Repository:** Cloned to `C:\\Autoresearch\\autoresearch\\`\n- **Guardian Scripts:** In `C:\\Autoresearch\\`\n- **Data Cache:** `~/.cache/autoresearch/` (BPE tokenizer + shards)\n- **Configuration:** Environment variables set (TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN, TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID)\n\n---\n\n**Project State:** READY TO RESUME  \n**Recommended Action:** Adjust hyperparameters for GTX 980M, then start 5-min test  \n**Estimated Time to First Successful Run:** 15 minutes  \n**Estimated Time to Overnight Run:** 30 minutes (after successful test)\n\n---\n\n*Paused for break. All systems configured and tested. Resume with hardware-specific adjustments.*\n","path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-31.md"}},{"type":"text","text":"  "}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"kimi-k2-thinking","usage":{"input":190180,"output":1784,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":191964,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774999711996}}
